dataIdInfo.idAbs:
The Benthic Terrain Modeler (BTM) v3.0 toolbox for ArcGIS is a collection of Esri ArcGIS-based tools that coastal and marine resource managers can use in concert with bathymetric data sets to examine and classify the benthic environment. The BTM toolbox contains a set of customized scripts that allow users to create grids of bathymetric position index (BPI), standardized BPIs, slope, and rugosity from an input bathymetric data set. Additionally, two terrain classification scripts give users the freedom to create their own zone and structure classifications and define the relationships that characterize them.

The BTM toolbox creates a user-defined classification system of benthic terrain. The BTM scripts transform digital elevation data into a classified product for use in research or natural resource management. However, the principles behind the tool are general enough that it can be used on any digital elevation data. The inclusion of flexible and customizable terrain classifications allows investigators and managers to create terrain maps in a variety of environments.

param.name: Output_Workspace
param.dialogReference: A defined workspace is required for the BTM model to place the output layers without having to type the paths for each output layer. Set the desired workspace and all of the output layers will be located centrally in one folder.
param.pythonReference: A defined workspace is required for the BTM model to place the output layers without having to type the paths for each output layer. Set the desired workspace and all of the output layers will be located centrally in one folder.

param.name: Bathymetry_raster
param.dialogReference: Input Bathymetric raster, can be of any type supported by ArcGIS. Expected values are negative elevation (depths) for bathymetric applications.
param.pythonReference: Input Bathymetric raster, can be of any type supported by ArcGIS. Expected values are negative elevation (depths) for bathymetric applications.

param.name: broad-scale_BPI_inner_radius
param.dialogReference:
Inner radius value of annulus-shaped analysis neighborhood in cells.

Broad-scale BPI data sets have larger analysis neighborhoods, and thus a larger scale factor. These data sets are useful in identifying larger benthic terrain regions or areas.

param.name: Classification_dictionary
param.dialogReference: The classification dictionary specifies classes based on ranges of the input BPI rasters and slope. These are usually CSV or Excel Spreadsheets, but the tool can also import legacy XML dictionaries created with previous versions of the tool. See example dictionary for an example of one such classification.
